## COMMAND ENGINE — v0.9.1 (commandRouter.ts v1.5.1)

### Design Philosophy
Karl decides everything. No word lists, no state machine. Every message goes to Karl — including
when a pending action exists. Karl sees the full picture and returns an intent.

### Data Flow
```
User types anything
→ workspace sends { input, pending, context_filter }
→ route.ts calls buildKarlContextSplit(user_id, context_filter)
→ formatStaticContextForPrompt() → system block (cached)
→ formatDynamicContextForPrompt() → prepended to last user message
→ routeCommand(user_id, input, pending, context_filter, [], { staticContext, dynamicContext })
→ Karl receives: input + pending payload + full context bundle
→ Karl returns intent (always JSON)
→ route/workspace executes
```

### Intent Types
- `execute` — Quick capture. Karl writes immediately, no confirm step.
- `pending` — Karl proposes action. Workspace sets pending state.
- `modify_pending` — User changed something. Complete updated payload returned. Tag enrichment SKIPPED.
- `confirm_pending` — Karl detected confirmation. Route executes pending payload.
- `cancel_pending` — Karl detected cancellation. Workspace clears pending.
- `preview_pending` — User asked what pending looks like. Pending stays alive.
- `open_form` — User wants full form. Workspace opens appropriate modal.
- `question` — Karl answers conversationally. Pending state NEVER touched.
- `command` — System command. Currently: `open_tag_manager`.
- `unclear` — Last resort. Karl should almost never return this.

### Actions Karl Can Propose
```
insert, update, complete, archive, delete, delete_object,
refine, run_template, save_as_template, capture_tasks, create_tag, summarize
```

### run_template Flow Rules (CRITICAL)
- "run TM1" with no mode → Karl ALWAYS asks preview or generate first. NON-NEGOTIABLE.
- "preview TM1" → skip step 1, go straight to `run_mode: preview`
- "generate TM1" / "run TM1 save" → skip step 1, go to `run_mode: generate` with section_data from default_scope
- preview executes immediately via `executeTemplateDraftRun` in page.tsx — does NOT go through pending
- generate goes through pending for section_data confirmation
- `flattenLegacyPending` — explicit `run_template` handler. NEVER falls through to insert task.
- `confirm_pending` handler in route.ts — forces `run_mode: generate` on any `run_template` action (safety net)

### Pending State — CRITICAL FIX (v0.9.0)
- `pending` in page.tsx now carries `actions[]` array — NOT just `payload`
- `pendingForKarl` sends `{ actions: pending.actions, action: pending.intent, ...pending.payload }`
- `flattenLegacyPending` reads `pending.actions?.length` first — this is how it finds the real actions
- **Root cause of phantom task creation:** pendingForKarl was sending null payload, flattenLegacyPending
  fell through to insert task. Fixed by carrying actions array through pending state.

### JSON Parse Fallback (v0.9.1)
Karl must always return valid JSON. When parse fails, the fallback only accepts responses with a valid `intent` field — preventing malformed partial matches from triggering phantom inserts:

```typescript
} catch {
  const jsonMatch = text.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);
  if (jsonMatch) {
    try {
      const candidate = JSON.parse(jsonMatch[0]);
      if (candidate?.intent) parsed = candidate;  // MUST have intent
    } catch { /* fall through */ }
  }
}
```

### Template Draft State (v0.9.0)
- `templateDraft` state in page.tsx — isolated from pending, lives for duration of template work session
- Interface: `{ templateId, identifier, instructions, output, running, name }`
- Preview mode executes immediately via `executeTemplateDraftRun()` — bypasses pending entirely
- Generate mode uses pending with full actions array intact

### Delete Rules
- `delete_object` always pending, never silent. Always include `display_name` in fields.
- Double-gated: commandRouter checks `allow_delete` + `executeDeleteObject` re-verifies at execution
- If not allowed: "Delete on [object type] disabled by administrator."

### Enrichment
On `pending` (not `modify_pending`): `suggestTagsForCapture()` makes a second lightweight Anthropic
call to suggest tags. Runs on `capture_task` AND `capture_tasks`. Skipped for `run_template` actions.
On `modify_pending`: enrichment skipped — user has explicitly set values.

### Context Filter Flow
`context_filter` (UUID or null) sent from workspace with every command.
Passed to `routeCommand()` → `buildKarlContext()` → task query filtered to match UI view.
Passed to `resolveIdentifier()` → identifier positions match filtered list user sees.

