## DEV RULES

- Architecture changes require explicit discussion before coding
- **Always generate complete files — never patch. Patching causes drift, duplicate declarations, and brace mismatches.**
- Field metadata is source of truth — never hardcode field behavior in UI
- Field metadata column is `field` not `field_name`
- Field metadata unique constraint: `(user_id, object_type, field)`
- Bucket colors hardcoded in UI — labels/icons from concept_registry
- Bucket identifiers hardcoded in UI and buildKarlContext — never from DB
- Concept registry is a system table — never query by user_id, always by implementation_type
- Backend is authority — DB is source of truth
- ko_user PK is `id` not `user_id`
- Tags stored as raw names NOT UUIDs
- context_id is a lightweight FK, not a scope parent
- `createSupabaseAdmin()` for backend, `supabase` client for frontend
- Always read current file before modifying — never patch from memory
- FC modals: white background, colored header, draggable, resizable, position initialized centered
- All modals use absolute positioning (no centered/transform pattern — causes jump on close)
- FC modal pattern: list left, edit right — clicking list item loads directly into edit form
- Anthropic API called via raw fetch, NOT @anthropic-ai/sdk (not installed)
- Routing model: `claude-sonnet-4-20250514`
- Generation model: `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` (document output only)
- **EVERY new Anthropic call must include prompt caching + token logging — no exceptions**
- Chat: Karl suggests from existing tags only — never creates tags via chat
- task.delegated_to is a uuid FK to People tag — resolved server-side via fuzzy name matching
- meeting.attendees is a REAL COLUMN (text[]) — separate from meeting.tags
- notes/description NEVER in generation prompts or API payloads — display-only
- section_data keys must exactly match sections[].key values — case sensitive
- default_scope lives inside sections[] JSONB — no separate DB column
- One-way flow: template.default_scope → extract.section_data (no bleedback ever)
- run_template preview path: executes immediately, never goes through pending state
- run_template generate path: goes through pending with full actions[] array intact
- Dynamic context (task snapshot, pending, date) goes in last user message — NEVER in system block
- Static context (field knowledge, tags, concept registry, Karl instructions) goes in system block with cache_control

